    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "algolia_search.js\r\n```js\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n    instantsearch.widgets.searchBox({\r\n      container: '.pw_st_search_search',\r\n      placeholder: '',\r\n    })\r\n  );\r\n```\r\nin php template:\r\n```html\r\n<script>\r\n    var client = algoliasearch('correct key', 'correct api');\r\n    var index = client.initIndex('correct index');\r\n    autocomplete('.pw_st_search_search',\r\n    { hint: true }, {\r\n    source: autocomplete.sources.hits(index, {hitsPerPage: 5}),\r\n    displayKey: 'name',\r\n    templates: {\r\n        suggestion: function(suggestion) {\r\n          //console.log(suggestion);\r\n          return '<span>' + suggestion._highlightResult.name.value + '</span><span>';\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n});\r\n</script>\r\n```\r\nI cant show you our original input because it is too dynamically generated but with this input is the same issue:\r\n```html\r\n<div class=\"aa-input-container\" id=\"aa-input-container\">\r\n      <input type=\"search\" id=\"\" class=\".pw_st_search_search aa-input-search\" placeholder=\"Search \" name=\"search\" autocomplete=\"on\" />\r\n</div>\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
