    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hmm i make it work but i don't know why ;). I move this part to our header, and autocomplete start working.\r\n```\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/algoliasearch/3/algoliasearch.min.js\"></script>\r\n\t <script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/autocomplete.js/0/autocomplete.min.js\"></script>\r\n\t <script>\r\n\t\tvar client = algoliasearch('NNWYKHZ90Y', 'd052c2a715d25707636e3a29d145e9e9');\r\n\t\tvar index = client.initIndex('prod_query_suggestions');\r\n\t\tautocomplete('.pw_st_search_search',\r\n\t\t{ hint: true }, {\r\n\t\tsource: autocomplete.sources.hits(index, {hitsPerPage: 5}),\r\n\t\tdisplayKey: 'query',\r\n\t\ttemplates: {\r\n\t\t\tsuggestion: function(suggestion) {\r\n\t\t\t  console.log(suggestion);\r\n\t\t\t  return '<span>' + suggestion._highlightResult.query.value + '</span>';\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t});\r\n\t</script>\r\n```\r\nBut search box stop working. Then I change widget container to another class of input like this:\r\n```\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n    instantsearch.widgets.searchBox({\r\n      container: '.aa-input',\r\n      placeholder: '',\r\n    })\r\n  );\r\n```\r\nAnd now work autocomplete and searching simultaneously ",
